Ordered take out via Doordash and the food arrived very hot and promptly.  The quality of food was sub par.  The sesame chicken tasted as if it had been fried in donut batter and for the majority of the pieces - you could not find chicken (only dough).  The side of fried rice was rice and egg with 2-3 pieces of minced pork.  The beef broccoli chow mein was very VERY bland.  I could not differentiate the taste of noodle, the sauce, or the meat.  Unfortunately I would not go back - I could not eat either of the meals.  Through doordash it was $40 for this meal.  Not worth it either way.  Panda Express quality is way better if your in a dinner bind (and healthier fry batter/oil).  Better yet - cook anything in your fridge and it will turn out with more flavor than what I purchased.

Used to be delicious. I am disappointed with the lunch plate.  It lacked the taste of the usual sweet sour ribs, kau yuk and their sauted veggies with noodles DIDN'T HAVE NOODLES.  The meat, although soft was still chewy - how does that happen? It's not the same. The price is not worth the taste. And they give less than what they used to. I haven't been there in years because I've moved. I don't know if it's the same family who owns it but not the same flavor. I miss the older lady who used to be there. She didn't smile but we didn't mind because she served good food that made us come back again and again ... not anymore.

Food is delicious and in generous portions, prices are better than Golden Duck, menu has a little of everything, and the service is excellent. There is enough parking at night, though I note the shabu shabu place next door is very popular.  From a business perspective, I am not sure who is the owner but he or she changes the employees every 5 years. My family friend was offered the opportunity to sign a 5 year lease but decided against it and someone else got it. The wait staff gets new people (might be the same persons who signed the lease), the menu has a makeover, and the decor also changes.

Hidden gem near Waikiki in my opinion. Came here with a group of 7 an hour before they close and we had the best service and really good food. Their menu is huge and filled with goodies that are super affordable compared to other places. On this night, we tried their wonton noodle soup (6.50$), and their Golden Eagle Special (39.99$) that comes with 4 entries and rice. The food was excellent and the Golden Eagle Special is a hit and highly recommended if you come with a large group. The portion size is spot on and flavor of each dish is just quality. I can't stop commenting on how great their service was. Our waitress or shall I say multiple waitresses were attentive and hands down provided the best service I've had in Hawaii. People needs to come here and try their food. Trust me, you won't be disappointed.
